---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import GalleryItem from '../components/GalleryItem.astro';
import AreaCard from '../components/AreaCard.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Buying a Home in Sonoma County Wine Country | Attorney Buyer's Agent Guide"
  description="Discover the beauty and lifestyle of Sonoma County wine country. Explore Healdsburg, Sonoma Valley, Petaluma, Sebastopol, Santa Rosa, and the Sonoma Coast."
  keywords="buying home Sonoma County wine country, buy home Healdsburg attorney help, Sonoma Valley home buyer legal representation, first time buyer Sonoma County attorney, buy vineyard Sonoma County legal help, relocate Bay Area to Sonoma County attorney buyer agent, Petaluma home buyer attorney, Sebastopol home buyer attorney"
>
    <section style="margin-top: 120px;">
        <h1 class="section-title">Sonoma County Real Estate & Wine Country Living</h1>
        <p class="section-subtitle">Discover the beauty and lifestyle that awaits in California's premier wine country.</p>

        <div class="gallery">
            <GalleryItem
                src="/photos/federico-sunset-field.jpg"
                alt="Golden sunset over rolling fields in Sonoma County"
                title="Golden Sunsets"
                description="Breathtaking evenings over the countryside"
            />
            <GalleryItem
                src="/photos/karol-rolling-hills.jpg"
                alt="Rolling hills with farmhouse in Sonoma County"
                title="Rolling Hills"
                description="Picturesque landscapes at every turn"
            />
            <GalleryItem
                src="/photos/jim-wine-cellar.jpg"
                alt="Wine barrel cellar at a Sonoma County winery"
                title="Wine Heritage"
                description="World-class wineries and wine caves"
            />
            <GalleryItem
                src="/photos/balloon-over-vineyard.jpg"
                alt="Hot air balloon over vineyard in Sonoma County wine country"
                title="Above the Vines"
                description="Experience the magic of Sonoma from above"
            />
            <GalleryItem
                src="/photos/tyke-mustard-vineyard.jpg"
                alt="Vineyard rows with yellow mustard flowers in Sonoma County"
                title="Mustard Season"
                description="Wildflowers bloom between the vines each spring"
            />
            <GalleryItem
                src="/photos/richard-vineyard-storm.jpg"
                alt="Vineyard at dramatic stormy sunset in Sonoma County"
                title="Dramatic Skies"
                description="Storm clouds roll over Sonoma's rolling vineyards"
            />
            <GalleryItem
                src="/photos/hari-vineyard-sunset.jpg"
                alt="Vineyard at golden sunset in Sonoma County"
                title="Harvest Season"
                description="Golden light over the vines at day's end"
            />
            <GalleryItem
                src="/photos/lisha-vineyard-cypress.jpg"
                alt="Vineyard with cypress trees and mountains in Sonoma County"
                title="Scenic Estates"
                description="Cypress-lined lanes through California wine country"
            />
            <GalleryItem
                src="/photos/ken-balloons-aerial.jpg"
                alt="Multiple hot air balloons over Sonoma County wine country"
                title="Above the Valley"
                description="A fleet of balloons soaring over Sonoma's wine country"
            />
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top: 4rem; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem;">
            <AreaCard name="Healdsburg" description="Upscale town square, Michelin-starred restaurants, boutique wineries, and Russian River access. Premium real estate in the heart of wine country." />
            <AreaCard name="Sonoma Valley" description="Historic plaza, walkable downtown, renowned wineries, and family-friendly neighborhoods. The birthplace of California wine." />
            <AreaCard name="Petaluma" description="Victorian architecture, river town charm, excellent schools, and easy Bay Area access. More affordable entry point to Sonoma living." />
            <AreaCard name="Sebastopol" description="Arts community, apple orchards, farmers markets, and eclectic downtown. Bohemian atmosphere meets wine country lifestyle." />
            <AreaCard name="Santa Rosa" description="County seat with urban amenities, diverse neighborhoods, shopping, dining, and cultural venues. Central location for exploring the region." />
            <AreaCard name="Sonoma Coast" description="Dramatic coastline, rugged beaches, cool climate wines, and stunning views. Peaceful retreat from wine country bustle." />
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 4rem; padding: 3rem; background: var(--white); border-radius: 4px; box-shadow: 0 4px 30px var(--shadow);">
            <h2 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">What Buyers Need to Know Before Purchasing in Sonoma County</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-light); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Sonoma County is not a standard suburban market. Each area has its own legal landscape — regulations, water rights, zoning overlays, and local ordinances that directly affect what you can do with a property after you buy it. Here is what matters most by area.</p>

            <div style="display: grid; gap: 2rem;">
                <div style="border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); padding-left: 1.5rem;">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Buying a Home or Estate in Healdsburg</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8;">Healdsburg commands premium prices and attracts buyers from across California and nationally. Many properties are close to the Russian River, raising flood zone and water rights questions. Wine-producing estates require review of agricultural water allocations and easements. These are areas where an attorney-broker's legal background is particularly relevant.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); padding-left: 1.5rem;">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Buying Vineyard or Rural Land in Sonoma County</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8;">Rural land purchases — vineyards, farms, or large parcels — involve water rights, well permits, PTRA (Public Trust Review Area) ordinances, agricultural easements, and access rights that most agents do not fully understand. These are legal issues, not just real estate issues, and they benefit from attorney-level analysis.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); padding-left: 1.5rem;">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Buying a Home in Petaluma or Sebastopol as a First-Time Buyer</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8;">Petaluma and Sebastopol offer more accessible price points for first-time buyers relocating from the Bay Area. But even at lower price points, California purchase contracts are complex legal documents. A first-time buyer represented by an attorney-broker enters the transaction with the same legal protection as a sophisticated investor.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); padding-left: 1.5rem;">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Buying a Vacation Rental Property in Sonoma County</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8;">Sonoma County's vacation rental permit system is frequently misunderstood. Permits are tied to the property owner — not the property — and may not transfer with a sale. Buyers who assume they can operate a short-term rental after closing have learned this lesson the hard way. Permit status is among the due diligence items worth investigating before closing.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 2.5rem; text-align: center;">
                <a href="/contact/" class="cta-button">Schedule a Free Buyer Consultation</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
